text.paragraph:
Useful also in the control of extrapyramidal disorders (except tardive dyskinesia – see 
                        PRECAUTIONS
                     ) due to neuroleptic drugs (e.g., phenothiazines).

Antipsychotic drugs such as phenothiazines or haloperidol; tricyclic antidepressants (see 
                              WARNINGS
                           ).

Because of the atropine-like side effects, benztropine mesylate should be used with caution in pediatric patients over three years of age (see 
                              CONTRAINDICATIONS
                           ).
